items.headline: Welcome to the SuperFriends Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the SuperFriends Wiki! This site is dedicated to Hanna-Barbera's Super Friends that aired on ABC from 1973-1985. The Super Friends roster consisted of a core group of characters central to the spirit of comic book heroism: Superman, Batman, Robin, Aquaman and Wonder Woman. Throughout the different seasons, they began to include other DC Comics characters such as the Flash, Green Lantern and Hawkman. Enter now to learn more about SuperFriends!

items.name: Thomas & Friends Wiki
items.title: Thomas & Friends Wiki
items.headline: Visit the magical Island of Sodor, the home of Thomas and his friends!
items.desc:
Thomas & Friends is a British children's television series, first broadcast on the ITV network on 4 September 1984. It is based on The Railway Series of books by the Reverend Wilbert Awdry and his son Christopher Awdry. These books deal with the adventures of a group of anthropomorphised trains and road vehicles who live on the fictional Island of Sodor. The books were based on stories Awdry told to entertain his son Christopher during his recovery from measles. Many of the stories are based on events from Awdry's personal experience.

The Railway Series is a set of story books about a railway system located on the fictional Island of Sodor. There are 42 books in the series, the first being published in 1945. Twenty-six were written by the Rev. W. (Wilbert) Awdry, up to 1972. A further 16 were written by his son, Christopher Awdry.
